Please accept this expression of our warm love for you, your brothers, the 150-second class of Gilead.

00:27:41.200 --> 00:27:47.039
Well, it's been a privilege to be able to come and visit you and give some lectures for your Gilead

00:27:47.039 --> 00:27:52.880
class, and I've always enjoyed it, but now I have a special privilege to speak first time

00:27:53.440 --> 00:27:59.680
to the graduates of the 150-second class. That seems an awesome thought, doesn't it?

00:27:59.680 --> 00:28:05.599
And we're glad that you made it this far. We know there's been a lot of hard work that's gone into it.

00:28:06.640 --> 00:28:13.440
So what final comments will we like to give you? We've had so many good things on the program,

00:28:13.519 --> 00:28:20.240
already today, haven't you? And even if we were a little bit overwhelmed and you were worried about

00:28:20.240 --> 00:28:24.880
certain aspects of the program, at least you can watch it on J.W. Broadcasting later

00:28:25.839 --> 00:28:31.519
and get the main points. But remember, in the beginning, we talked about the need for us to be

00:28:31.519 --> 00:28:40.799
modest, to be enthusiastic, but patient. And we remember how Jesus said a wonderful example for us in

00:28:41.759 --> 00:28:48.640
acknowledging humbly that he had an assignment and that he put that assignment first in his life.

00:28:48.640 --> 00:28:55.519
But he also showed wonderful balance, didn't he? When the Sorrow of Phoenician woman begged him to

00:28:55.519 --> 00:29:01.359
help her because of her expression of faith in accepting him as the Messiah, he was willing to

00:29:01.359 --> 00:29:09.200
be flexible. And she got what a wonderful blessing she got. And then the Roman officer,

00:29:09.200 --> 00:29:17.440
the Samaritan woman, all these people were ones who really technically weren't part of his

00:29:17.440 --> 00:29:23.920
territory and yet they got wonderful blessings because they asked especially for some help.

00:29:24.880 --> 00:29:30.000
Well, what's the lessons for us? Well, maybe before we go on to the lessons, we could think of

00:29:30.000 --> 00:29:36.400
some of the other non-Isolites who gained some benefit from Jesus' ministry. Who else would you

00:29:36.400 --> 00:29:46.240
think of? What about Pontius Pilate and those in his court when he had all these discussions?

00:29:46.960 --> 00:29:53.200
Well, now I'm not telling you that Pontius Pilate benefited from it, but we do see that he had a

00:29:53.200 --> 00:30:01.279
wonderful opportunity, didn't he? Because he is a sort of person, a very violent man, a person who

00:30:01.440 --> 00:30:08.319
at the drop of a hat had someone executed and yet what do we see over and over again? He seemed to

00:30:08.319 --> 00:30:14.720
try and avoid sentencing Jesus to death. Well, we know that something impressed him. Again,

00:30:14.720 --> 00:30:19.680
is this one of the times when Jesus spoke in Greek to him or some other language? Who knows?

00:30:20.319 --> 00:30:28.000
I'm not speculating. But we do know that he was very impressed. And what about those that were

00:30:28.640 --> 00:30:36.240
there listening? There was a lot going on. Well, remember later when Jesus actually died, there was

00:30:36.240 --> 00:30:44.880
a Centurion. And the Centurion acknowledged that this was the Son of God. The study note, if you

00:30:44.880 --> 00:30:51.519
check it later, says, maybe he was there with Pontius Pilate. That makes sense, doesn't he? He was

00:30:51.519 --> 00:31:00.240
perhaps in charge of organizing this. So that man got a tremendous benefit from at least seeing

00:31:00.240 --> 00:31:07.279
Jesus and hearing his testimony. And on his right was someone who gained benefit. And then finally,

00:31:07.279 --> 00:31:11.680
what about those two Roman soldiers that witnessed the resurrection? Now, they didn't have a

00:31:11.680 --> 00:31:17.920
chance to talk to Jesus as far as we know, but they did see the angel roll back the stone. What

00:31:17.920 --> 00:31:24.240
is the impact that would have had on their lives? So thinking about these ones that we've just

00:31:24.240 --> 00:31:29.759
discussed, what do we see? Well, when you go back to your assignments, as we mentioned,

00:31:30.400 --> 00:31:36.160
there'll be the temptation to get yourself involved with everything he's going on to visit the

00:31:36.160 --> 00:31:43.119
90 islands to get a ship. No, I know you're not going to do that. But the temptation will be there

00:31:43.200 --> 00:31:50.319
to sort of see the need to help as many people as possible. But what's the point? Remember,

00:31:50.319 --> 00:31:56.240
you have an assignment. Each one of you now has a specific assignment. Put that first, be faithful,

00:31:56.960 --> 00:32:02.480
loyal to Jehovah. Apply all these things that you've not only heard in Gilead, but also in today's

00:32:02.480 --> 00:32:09.440
program. And there'll be patient. Leave it to Jehovah. Remember, it's Jehovah's work, isn't it?

00:32:09.440 --> 00:32:14.000
I remember one dear brother of the governing body made the comment once, you know, when he was

00:32:14.000 --> 00:32:22.559
facing a difficult situation. He just looked and said, it's Jehovah's problem. And that's what we

00:32:22.559 --> 00:32:30.240
need to recognize. Some things we leave to Jehovah. So as you go, we wish you Jehovah's blessing.

00:32:30.240 --> 00:32:40.799
Remember, be enthusiastic. But also, be patient.
